With the Premier League season now officially underway, many top-flight clubs have had the first taste of the things they are missing within their squads. As a result it's now very much scramble time, with transfers expected to come thick and fast as deadline day approaches. Manchester United got their season off to a disasterous start with home defeat to Brighton, and their lack of both firepower and an anchor in the centre of midfield is glaringly obvious. Elsewhere, Chelsea failed to flatter as they scraped a 1-0 victory over Everton, with Thomas Tuchel himself admitting at the final whistle that more signings are almost certainly needed. Tuchel and Erik ten Hag aren't the only managers pushing for more backing in the summer transfer market, meaning plenty more deals could be done over the coming weeks. FOLLOW EXPRESS SPORT'S LIVE TRANSFER UPDATES BELOW... 